  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "If a mirror pod gets deleted for some reason, the status won't ever be updated since the pod status appears the same.\n\nWe used to solve this issue by deleting the pod status. This is undesirable because many internal kubelet components relying on the pod status for various operations. I think we can add a function to forcibly increment the version of the status when creating a new mirror pod.\n\n/cc @timstclair \n",
